column17:
[{'answer': 'ADF deployment and AZ setup prep for employer interview upcoming. Previous convo related to this interview is here https://seanpcomptong-i397423.slack.com/archives/C09GL5NV77G/p1765568620628249

Ninad recommended scheduling time to prep together, you were very helpful on my previous interview as well.

Client panel interview will ask:

The next step is a technical panel interview with some potential future colleagues.
Normally we would base the interview around discussion of a take home assignment. We dont have a formal coding assessment for Data Engineer, so if you have a repo in your GitHub that you feel is a good example of your coding style, or you otherwise have a sample of code to share, please send to Ben (to distribute to the panel) at least a day before the interview.
To give the panel interview some structure, consider the following fictional setup, and give some thought to the topics mentioned. The panel interviewers may have further questions to ask.
A company has a product with multiple components and multiple customers. Each component has its own Azure SQL Server database.
What are some considerations for implementing a multi- vs single-tenant solution for handling customer data, especially when it comes to handling customers with different data aggregation rights?
Are there situations in which it is appropriate for some components of the product to be multi-tenant while others are single-tenant?
There are Azure Data Factory (ADF) pipelines to sync production data from the SQL databases to parquet files on Azure Blob Storage. As new tenants are deployed, new ADF pipelines must also be deployed.
What are some considerations on choosing between Terraform, Bicep, or Python scripts for programmatically deploying ADF pipelines?
How do you monitor for, and adapt to, changes in the SQL database schemas?
Databricks is used as a development environment for exploration, analysis, model building, and ETL pipelines to reporting.
What are some considerations for programmatically defining external tables in Databricks over the parquet files in Azure Blob Storage?
What are some considerations for testing the Databricks pipelines, especially those that lead to customer-facing reports? 
Some of the columns in the data contain complex JSON structures. What are some considerations for choosing whether to explode this JSON in an ADF pipeline or Databricks pipeline?
What documentation do you consider to be critical at each stage, both for people working on the end-to-end pipeline and for people who are purely consumers of the tables in Databricks?

Ninad helped provide me these questions to prepare:
Multi-tenant vs single-tenant (and mixed models)
We have customers with different aggregation rights (some can see only their tenant, some can see rollups across a group). How would you design row-level security end-to-end (SQL  parquet  Databricks  reporting)?
When would you choose one database per tenant vs shared database with tenant_id, given cost, isolation, and ops overhead?
What failure modes have you seen with multi-tenant ETL (e.g., one noisy tenant delaying pipelines)? How do you prevent them?
How do you handle tenant offboarding / right-to-be-forgotten when data is in parquet + derived tables?
In what cases would you keep operational components single-tenant but run analytics multi-tenant (or the opposite)? Give a concrete example.
How would you implement tenant-level encryption / key management in Azure for stricter customers?
How do you structure naming conventions and resource groups so tenant deployments dont become a mess after 50200 customers?
ADF pipeline deployment (Terraform vs Bicep vs Python)
If a new tenant needs 30+ pipelines and linked services, how do you avoid copy-paste JSON drift across environments?
Compare Terraform vs Bicep for ADF in practice: what breaks, whats hard to diff/review, whats hard to roll back?
When would you deliberately use Python scripts (e.g., SDK / REST calls) instead of IaC for ADF deployments?
How do you manage secrets (SQL creds, storage keys, service principals) across tenants and environments?
Whats your approach for CI/CD for ADF: publish branch, ARM templates, Git mode, release pipelineswhat do you actually prefer and why?
If one tenant needs a slightly different pipeline (custom extraction window / extra table), how do you keep it config-driven rather than forking pipelines?
Schema change detection and adaptation
How do you detect schema changes in Azure SQL before they break the ingestion job?
Whats your stance on schema evolution for parquet (add columns, change types, nested JSON changes)?
Describe a practical approach to contract testing between producers (product DBs) and consumers (Databricks/reporting).
If a column changes type (INT  BIGINT, or string  enum), what is your migration plan that avoids breaking reports?
How do you version and publish data models (bronze/silver/gold) so downstream users can rely on stability?
Databricks external tables over parquet (Blob / ADLS)
Would you use external tables, managed tables, or Delta on top of parquetand why? (Cost, VACUUM, time travel, compaction, governance.)
How do you organize storage paths for multi-tenant data to support partition pruning and access controls?
How do you handle small files from ADF landing into blob (the classic issue)? Whats your compaction strategy?
How do you manage schema-on-read vs schema-on-write in Databricks for reliability?
How do you implement permissions so analysts cant accidentally read other tenants (Unity Catalog, table ACLs, storage ACLs)?
Testing pipelines that feed customer-facing reports
What does testing mean for data pipelines in your world: unit tests, data quality checks, reconciliation, or end-to-end snapshots?
How do you test that a report pipeline is correct when source data is changing daily?
What are 35 data quality rules youd enforce at the silver/gold layers for customer-facing reporting?
How would you set up canary tenants or staged rollouts for pipeline changes?
How do you prevent it passed but numbers changed regressionsdo you do metric diffs / expected aggregates?
JSON columns: explode in ADF vs Databricks
When would you keep JSON as a raw column vs explode into relational columns? Talk about query patterns and schema volatility.
Compare exploding JSON in ADF mapping data flows vs in Databricks: maintainability, observability, performance, cost.
How do you handle late-arriving keys in JSON (new attributes appear mid-week)?
What do you do when JSON is dirty / inconsistent (same key sometimes string sometimes object)?
Monitoring, observability, and incident response
Whats your monitoring setup across ADF + Databricks? What alerts matter (freshness, volume anomalies, failure rate, SLA breaches)?
How do you do lineage: this report number came from these tables and these runs?
A customer says: Yesterdays report is wrong. Walk us through your debug playbook.
How do you manage reprocessing/backfills safely without double-counting?
What metrics do you track per tenant (cost, runtime, data size) to prevent surprises?
Documentation and operational readiness
What docs must exist before a pipeline goes live? (Runbooks, ownership, SLAs, data dictionary, lineage, escalation path.)
What documentation do you provide to pure consumers (analysts/CS/report users) so they dont misinterpret metrics?
How do you document aggregation rights and business rules so theyre auditable and consistently applied?
Whats your approach to data cataloging and making datasets discoverable?
How do you keep docs up to datewhats automated vs manual?
Practical scenario questions (very common in panels)
You onboard 10 new tenants next month. Whats your plan to ensure deployments are repeatable, secure, and observable on day 1?
ADF loads are fine for most tenants but one tenant is 10 larger. How do you redesign ingestion without breaking everyone else?
A schema change shipped in production with no notice and pipelines broke at 2am. What changes do you implement to prevent a repeat?
Finance asks you to cut cloud spend by 25% without reducing SLAs. What optimizations do you look at first in ADF/Databricks/storage?', 'position': 0, 'question': 'Please share anything that will help prepare for our meeting.'}]
